latestPosts.caption:
I know I'm superrr late to this trend but it was one of my favourites. 

I do want to share more about my life and what experiences have shaped me into the person I am today and so I thought this trend was a great way to do that.

This is kind of like a letter to the past year me, I hope you all love it 💛

I've seen a bunch of reels going around talking about how therapists are turning children against their parents, and I don't think that's true. 

A therapist's job isn't to tell people what to do, but to ask the right questions that help them reflect and come to their own conclusions. 

Sometimes, that reflection leads to changes that can feel uncomfortable to those around them, but it's not about blame. 

It's about healing, growth, and learning to understand each other better 🪿

I know there are still 11 days left for this month to end, but honestly? It’s already been one of the most eye-opening ones for me.

I’ve spent a lot of time reflecting on my patterns, the way I connect with people, and what I’ve been choosing to hold onto. 

I used to think certain feelings meant something was right, like if someone made me feel seen or special, that must mean it was everything I needed. 

But now I see that sometimes, the magic you feel isn't coming from them, it's actually coming from you.

Real love, I’m learning, isn’t just about intense feelings or beautiful moments. It’s about being met fully, consistently, and genuinely. 

Not almost. Not halfway.

This month has helped me get clearer on what I’m willing to pour into, and more importantly, what truly pours back into me.

And that shift? It’s everything 🤍
